Config Supervisor:
1> must use pip to install, open python and type import supervisor to check
#output the default config file
2> echo_supervisord_conf > /etc/supervisord.conf
3> create own sub-config and add path in [include]
4> sudo supervisord -c path(config)
5> sudo supervisorctl -c path(config)
6> sudo supervisorctl reload
7> sudo supervisorctl start program name
8> sudo supervisorctl status

some command:
#check current supervisord process
1> ps aux | grep supervisord
2> sudo kill -s SIGTERM number

Reference link:
http://liyangliang.me/posts/2015/06/using-supervisor/
https://blog.csdn.net/wangjianwanxiao/article/details/51007354
